ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">reported last wee=
k</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Upstart private credit firm Corinthia Global M=
anagement approached Barings and parent MassMutual about buying certain Bar=
ings assets and overseeing some of its portfolios, after poaching more than=
 20 people from the firm, according to people with knowledge of the matter.=
 ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The new private credit manager also offered to=
 provide portfolio management services to Barings Global Private Finance, w=
hich includes Barings=E2=80=99 direct lending operations, and assume manage=
ment of its funds over time, subject to investor and regulatory approvals, =
the person said. The company also proposed sharing some revenues, the perso=
n added.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Discussions haven=E2=80=99t advanced and the t=
wo firms are not currently engaged in talks regarding the proposal, the peo=
ple said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Rude! This week <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/34754866.261362/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMTgvYmFyaW5ncy1zdGFydHMtbGVnYWwtYWN0aW9uLWF=
nYWluc3QtcHJpdmF0ZS1jcmVkaXQtZGVmZWN0b3JzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMjAyNF9NT05FWVNUVU=
ZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDMyM=
CZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBedba4887" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">Barings sued</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investment manager Barings sued Corinthia Glob=
al Management and former employees Ian Fowler and Kelsey Tucker after the u=
pstart private credit firm poached more than 20 employees in one of the lar=
gest team lifts at an alternative asset manager in recent years.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The poaching shocked the private credit indust=
ry, which has grown to $1.7 trillion in assets under management globally. T=
he industry has expanded quickly as more firms seek exposure to a corner of=
 the loan market that can appear less volatile and offer higher returns, bu=
t starting a new asset manager remains difficult given the limited talent p=
ool in the niche.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/34754866.261362/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvMzU5=
ZGM5OTEtNGU2OS00OWNjLThiMjUtY2U3NTQzOGQ2YTAx/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcd4ff=
043" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">Financial Times notes</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The raid, which one rival to Barings described=
 as =E2=80=9Caggressive=E2=80=9D and a tactic they had never seen before, c=
arries a risk that the loans Barings currently holds are refinanced by othe=
r lenders keen to take advantage of the situation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When private credit firms are willingly put up=
 for sale, it is not unusual for a quarter of that firm=E2=80=99s loan book=
 to be refinanced by rivals. It is potentially more fraught when a situatio=
n is hostile, the rival added.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CTypically this would create a run on =
the portfolio because anyone in those deals would try to refinance them out=
,=E2=80=9D the person said. =E2=80=9CAnd it raises bigger issues of how do =
[private equity] sponsors feel about them?=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Barings=E2=80=99 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/34754866.261362/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9=
kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3I1SlBjSG5FOURTay92MA/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB6748d24d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">complaint</a> explains how rude it was:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At 5:39 p.m. Eastern time on Friday, March 8 =
=E2=80=93 after 10:30 at night in London =E2=80=93 the founder of Corinthia=
, Paul Weightman, emailed Roger Crandall, the chairman and chief executive =
officer of Barings=E2=80=99 parent company, Massachusetts Mutual Life Insur=
ance Company (=E2=80=9CMassMutual=E2=80=9D), referencing Mr. Wheeler=E2=80=
=99s resignation and requesting to arrange a time to speak on Saturday, Mar=
ch 9.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the morning of March 9, Mr. Weightman again=
 emailed Mr. Crandall threatening that the impending departure of =E2=80=9C=
the senior managers will create a range of issues for the Barings Private C=
redit business=E2=80=9D and attaching an unsolicited term sheet pursuant to=
 which Corinthia sought to assume responsibility for Barings=E2=80=99 entir=
e GPF business, make offers of employment to all employees of the GPF group=
 and have Barings release all of those employees from their restrictive cov=
enants, and purchase the GPF portfolio and business for pennies on the doll=
ar. The Corinthia term sheet went so far as to provide that Barings would a=
ppoint Corinthia as the sub-investment advisor for Barings=E2=80=99 managed=
 funds and pay Corinthia a portion of the management fees earned by Barings=
 on the GPF funds.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Once you have the people, the loans are worth =
pennies on the dollar. Barings argues that its former employees are breachi=
ng their non-solicitation and confidentiality agreements, and you get a sen=
se of how important those agreements are. If the value of the business is j=
ust in the employees=E2=80=99 knowledge and relationships, and they can tak=
e that knowledge and those relationships with them, then what else did Bari=
ngs own?=C2=A0</p>
